<!---------------------------------------------------------------->
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>The Best MP3 Resources!</H2>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
This page contains technical resources related specifically to MPEG Audio Layer 3 (aka MP3).  Other MPEG Audio resources are listed on the <A HREF="audio.html">Audio</A> page.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<!---------------------------------------------------------------->
<CENTER>
<A HREF="#overview">MP3 Overview</A><BR>
<A HREF="#faqs">MP3 FAQs (Answers to Frequently Asked Questions)</A><BR>
<A HREF="#music">MP3 Music Resources</A><BR>
<A HREF="#search">MP3 Search Engines</A><BR>
<A HREF="#resources">MP3 Technical Resources</A><BR>
<A HREF="#softwares">MP3 Software (public-domain or free)</A><BR>
<A HREF="#test-bitstreams">MP3 Test Bitstreams</A><BR>
<A HREF="#links">MP3 Links</A><BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<BR>
<!---------------------------------------------------------------->
<H3><A NAME="overview">MP3 Overview</A></H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
More general MPEG Audio overviews can be found on the <A HREF="audio.html">Audio</A> page.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://ftp.fhg.de/pub/iis/layer3/MPEG_Audio_L3_FAQ.html#intro"><B>What is MPEG Audio Layer-3 ?</B></A> at Fraunhofer Institut<BR>A section of their larger FAQ.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="mp3-licensing.html"><B>MP3 Licensing Informations</B></A> <B><I>(new)</I></B>
</UL>
<!---------------------------------------------------------------->
<H3><A NAME="faqs">MP3 FAQs (Answers to Frequently Asked Questions)</A></H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
More general MPEG Audio FAQs can be found on the <A HREF="audio.html">Audio</A> page.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://ftp.fhg.de/pub/iis/layer3/MPEG_Audio_L3_FAQ.html"><B>Frequently Asked Questions about MPEG Audio Layer-3, Fraunhofer-IIS, and all the rest...</B></A> at Fraunhofer Institut (mirror <A HREF="http://www.iis.fhg.de/departs/amm/layer3/sw/index.html">here</A> and <A HREF="http://ds.dial.pipex.com/beast/mp3/faq.htm">here</A>)
</UL>
<!---------------------------------------------------------------->
<H3><A NAME="music">MP3 Music Resources</A></H3>
<UL>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://barista.stanford.edu/m3c">The MP3 Audio Consortium</A> by David E. Weekly<BR>(This site is (temporarily?) closed) A group promoting MP3 format for distribution of CD-quality music on the internet.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://ds.dial.pipex.com/beast/mp3/index.htm">MP3 - MPEG Layer 3 Audio</A> by Robbie Longworth<BR>Lots of interesting links and info.  Includes front-ends to various specialized search engines.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mp3site.com/">mp3site.com</A> by {python} and #mp3<BR>your only stop for anything to do with mp3's. Most people will tell you, if you can't find what you're looking for here, it doesn't exist..
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://members.visi.net/~flipino/layer3.html">MPEG-1 Audio Layer 3 Page</A> by Gary 'Flipino'<BR>Lots of annotated MP3 resources. CD Rippers, too.
</UL>
<!---------------------------------------------------------------->
<H3><A NAME="search">MP3 Search Engines</A></H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Those search engines can be used to locate MP3 audio clips available from the Net.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mp3.com/search.html">MP3.com Search Engine</A> by MP3.com <B><I>(new)</I></B><BR>
With links to other MP3 search engines.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://henrik.org/">MP3 4U Search Engine</A> by Henrik P Johnson <B><I>(new)</I></B>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mp3site.com/search.html">MP3 Search Engine</A> by #mp3<BR>Looks like the best way to find the MP3 clip you're looking for.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://ducttape.deeznuts.com/search/">MP3 Search Engine</A> by Ducttape Deeznuts<BR>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.nconnect.net/~vyper/">Vyper's MP3 search</A> by Jeff Peiffer and Vyper<BR>
Unfortunately this one advertises some porn sites.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://129.69.212.1/~hohlor/sql/mp3.html">The Chaos' MP3 search engine</A> by Oliver Hohl<BR>
Seems to be one of the bests.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://spam.cyberhighway.net/search/">MP3 Search-a-rooni</A> by Cyber Highway<BR>
</UL>
<!---------------------------------------------------------------->
<H3><A NAME="resources">MP3 Technical Resources</A></H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
More general MPEG Audio resources can be found on the <A HREF="audio.html">Audio</A> page.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.iis.fhg.de/departs/amm/layer3/index.html">MPEG Audio Layer 3</A> at Fraunhofer Institut<BR>The reference on MPEG Layer 3 compression technology.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.eskimo.com/~miyaguch/mp3info.html#How do I encode my own MP3 files">How do I encode my own MP3 files?</A> at Eskimo North<BR>A Guide for encoding MPEG AUdio Layer 3 with the tools from Fraunhofer Institute (<A HREF="http://members.aol.com/et3bahn/mp3/mp3info.html#How do I encode my own MP3 files">mirror here</A>).
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.lte.e-technik.uni-erlangen.de/~spo/eusipco.corrected.ps">The use of multirate filter banks for coding of high quality digital audio</A> by Th. Sporer, K. Brandenburg, and B. Edler (postscript)<BR>Describes the filterbank used in MP3 and gives an algorithm for a fast implementation of the MDCT (modified discrete cosine transform).
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mp3bench.com/">The Definitive MP3 Benchmark</A> by Cedric Amand <B><I>(new)</I></B><BR>
This site contains an extensive test of all known MP3 encoders and MP3
players. This includes an objective description and links to the web pages where
you can find the programs.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mpeg3.org/">The MPEG-1 Audio Layer 3 Directory</A> by Arc.Net<BR>
Access to MP3 FAQ and Software for various platforms.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mpeg3.org/">MPEG Resources</A> by The Realm of Soft Delusions<BR>Access to MP3 Encoders and players for various platforms.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mpeg1.de/layer3.html">MPEG-1 Audio Layer 3 streaming</A> at Phade Software
</UL>
<!---------------------------------------------------------------->
<H3><A NAME="softwares">MP3 Software (public-domain or free)</A></H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Only software supporting Layer 3 is listed here. MPEG Audio software that do not support Layer 3 can be found on the <A HREF="audio.html">Audio</A> page.
<P>
Many sites with pointers to MPEG audio players are listed on our <A HREF="MPEG-audio-player.html">Audio Players</A> Page.
<P>
<I>Before copying or using the following software, please check their <B>copyright</B> and <B>licence</B> informations.</I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://ftp.tnt.uni-hannover.de/pub/MPEG/audio/">MPEG-1 and MPEG-2 Audio reference software and data</A> (with source code) at Universitaet Hannover<BR>
This is the reference software produced by the MPEG Committee as draft of the Technical Report (Part-5 of the MPEG-1 and MPEG-2 standards).
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://home1.swipnet.se/%7Ew-10694/helpers.html#utilities">MPEG-1 Audio Layer 2 & 3 player (mpeg3play)</A> (with source code) by Johan Hagman<BR>
mpeg3play is an optimized version of the MPEG reference software that decodes Layer 3 in real-time (no graphic interface). Runs on several flavors of Unix and other platforms (also <A HREF="http://home1.swipnet.se/%7Ew-10694/tars/">here</A>).
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mpeg.org/xaudio/">Xaudio</A> by MpegTV<BR>
A fast player with a nice front-end. Layers 1, 2 and 3. Runs on a variety of platforms (windows, unix, bebox, etc).
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.msc.cornell.edu/~bef2/">A Linux Player For MPEG Audio (Tk3Play)</A> (with source code) by Brian Foutz at Cornell University<BR>
A version of maplay with an X-Window (Tk) front-end. Supports Layers 1, 2, and 3.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.telematik.informatik.uni-karlsruhe.de/~walther/index.html">MPEG-1 Audio Layer 2 & 3 for Windows 95 / NT 3.51 / NT 4.0 (museArc)</A> by Uli Walther & Stefan Kraus at Universitat Karlsruhe.<BR>
Check the <A HREF="http://www.telematik.informatik.uni-karlsruhe.de/~walther/musearc-docu.htm">Manual</A> (in german).
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www-inst.eecs.berkeley.edu/~ctsay/mp2win32.html">Maplay 1.2+ for Win32</A> (with source code) by Jeff Tsay<BR>
Nice GUI, plays Layer 1, 2 & 3.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://ftp.fhg.de/pub/layer3/public_c/">MPEG-1 Audio Layer 1, 2 & 3 decoder</A> (with source code) at Fraunhofer Institute<BR>
Decoder is not real-time on most machines.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.iis.fhg.de/departs/amm/layer3/index.html">MPEG-1 Audio Layer 3 encoder and player</A> at Fraunhofer Institut<BR>
Also <A HREF="ftp://ftp.fhg.de/pub/layer3">ftp site</A>.  Check this <A HREF="http://www.eskimo.com/~miyaguch/mp3.html#How do I encode my own MP3 files">User's Guide</A>.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://ftp.rasip.fer.hr/pub/mpeg/">Audio Mpeg Player (amp)</A>  (with source code) by Tomislav Uzelac at University of Zagreb<BR>
An MPEG Layer 3 Audio decoder for Linux and Solaris.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://tick.informatik.uni-stuttgart.de/~mutschml/MP3ext/MP3ext.html">MP3Ext</A> by Michael Mutschler<BR>
MP3Ext is an extension for the Windows Internet Explorer that adds
MP3-specific informations to the properties-menu of MP3-files: playlength,
bitrate, sample-frequency, and the ID3-Tag, if the file has got one.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://w3.teaser.fr/~mpollet/Vamp/">Vamp</A> by Michel Pollet<BR>
An MPEG Layer 3 Audio player for PowerMac based on amp.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://members.visi.net/~flipino/coders.html">flipTech Visual Encoder & Decoder</A> by flipino<BR>Visual Encoder and Visual Decoder are Windows95/NT frontends for the popular L3ENC and L3DEC utilities.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.anime.net/~go/mpeckers.html">MPeck MPEG Layer 3 Encoder for PPC Macintosh</A> by Rafael W. Luebbert<BR>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ctcusa.com/users/cburkey/mpeg/burkey.htm">Resonate</A> by Burkey consultants<BR>
A streaming Layer 2 and 3 MPEG player (<A HREF="http://www.ctcusa.com/users/cburkey/mpeg/resonate/">also here</A>).
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mpeg1.de/mpega.html">More MPEG Utilities</A> at Phade Software
<LI><A HREF="http://www.wp.com/101145/mpeg/audio.htm">MPEG Audio software</A> at MPEG Central
</UL>
<!---------------------------------------------------------------->
<H3><A NAME="test-bitstreams">MP3 Test Bitstreams</A></H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
Test bitstreams are specially designed
to help verify that an MPEG decoder works properly.
Conformance bitstreams are the official test bitstreams provided
by the MPEG committee.
<P>
Only Layer 3 test bitstreams are listed here. Other MPEG Audio test bitstreams can be found on the <A HREF="audio.html">Audio</A> page.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://ftp.fhg.de/pub/layer3">MPEG-1 Audio Layer 3 test bitstreams</A> at Fraunhofer Institut
</UL>
<!---------------------------------------------------------------->
<H3><A NAME="links">MP3 Links</A></H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
Links to MP3 sites with many links.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mp3.com/">MP3.com</A> <B><I>(new)</I></B> by Marcel Vogel<BR>
One on the most extensive MP3 website. Don't miss it!
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.rara.com/mp3/">mp3</A> <B><I>(new)</I></B> by Ralf Schaefer<BR>
How do you say MP3 in German ?
<P>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://ftp.fhg.de/pub/layer3">Daily Updated MP3 Software</A> <B><I>(new)</I></B> by Jimmy Gunawan
</UL>
<P>
